Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #medium saucepan with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press).

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Cut into 1cm chunks.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}.

Pop the pepper and shallot onto a #baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

While the veg roasts, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large saucepan on medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @korma curry paste{50%g}. Cook until fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @diced chicken breast{260%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1} and @water{100%ml}(for the curry). Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down and cover with a #lid.

Simmer until the chicken is cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @green chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed, then finely chop.

Remove the lid from the curry and stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @cashew butter{30%g} until well combined. Bring to the boil, then simmer for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain naans{2} onto a #baking tray. Spread over the @butter{20%g} and pop into the #oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, taste and season your curry with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls and top with your ultimate creamy chicken korma.

Spoon over the shallot and pepper topping, then finish with a sprinkle of green chilli (careful, it's hot).

Serve your buttery naans alongside. Enjoy!